(633, 225, '_pukka_dynamic_meta_box', 's:9023:\"a:15:{i:0;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:11:\"widget-area\";s:4:\"size\";s:3:\"100\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"content\";s:108:\"{\"data\":[{\"bg_color\":\"\",\"custom_classes\":\"column-3 boxed\",\"sidebar_id\":\"about-us\",\"text_color\":\"\"}],\"num\":0}\";}i:1;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"divider\";s:4:\"size\";s:3:\"100\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"content\";s:71:\"{\"data\":[{\"bg_color\":\"\",\"height\":\"50\",\"margin_top_bottom\":\"\"}],\"num\":0}\";}i:2;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:4:\"size\";s:3:\"100\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"content\";s:3559:\"{\"data\":[{\"bg_color\":\"\",\"text_content\":\"<div class=\\\"boxed\\\">\\n<p>HOW happy I am that I am gone! My dear friend, what a thing is the heart of man! To leave you, from whom I have been inseparable, whom I love so dearly, and yet to feel happy! I know you will forgive me. Have not other attachments been specially appointed by fate to torment a head like mine? Poor Leonora! and yet I was not to blame. Was it my fault, that, whilst the peculiar charms of her sister afforded me an agreeable entertainment, a passion for me was engendered in her feeble heart? And yet am I wholly blameless? Did I not encourage her emotions? Did I not feel charmed at those truly genuine expressions of nature, which, though but little mirthful in reality, so often amused us? Did I not&mdash;but oh! what is man, that he dares so to accuse himself? My dear friend, I promise you I will improve; I will no longer, as has ever been my habit, continue to ruminate on every petty vexation which fortune may dispense; I will enjoy the present, and the past shall be for me the past. No doubt you are right, my best of friends, there would be far less suffering amongst mankind, if men&mdash;and God knows why they are so fashioned&mdash;did not employ their imaginations so assiduously in recalling the memory of past sorrow, instead of bearing their present lot with equanimity. Be kind enough to inform my mother that I shall attend to her business to the best of my ability, and shall attend her the earliest information about it. I have seen my aunt, and find that she is very far from being the disagreeable person our friends allege her to be. She is a lively, cheerful woman, with the best of hearts. I explained to her my mother&rsquo;s wrongs with regard to that part of her portion which has been withheld from her. She told me the motives and reasons of her own conduct, and the terms on which she is willing to give up the whole, and to do more than we have asked. In short, I cannot write further upon this subject at present; only assure my mother that all will go on well. And I have again observed, my dear friend, in this trifling affair, that misunderstandings and neglect occasion more mischief in the world than even malice and wickedness. At all events, the two latter are of less frequent occurrence. In other respects I am very well off here. Solitude in this terrestrial paradise is a genial balm to my mind, and the young spring cheers with its bounteous promises my oftentimes misgiving heart. Every tree, every bush, is full of flowers; and one might wish himself transformed into a butterfly, to float about in this ocean of perfume, and find his whole existence in it. The town itself is disagreeable; but then, all around, you find an inexpressible beauty of Nature. This induced the late Count M&mdash;&mdash; to lay out a garden on one of the sloping hills which here intersect each other with the most charming variety, and form the most lovely valleys. The garden is simple; and it is easy to perceive, even upon your first entrance, that the plan was not designed by a scientific gardener, but by a man who wished to give himself up here to the enjoyment of his own sensitive heart Many a tear have I already shed to the memory of its departed master in a summer-house which is now reduced to ruins, but was his favourite resort, and now is mine. I shall soon be master of the place. The gardener has become attached to me within the last few days, and he will lose nothing thereby.</p>\\n</div>\",\"text_color\":\"\",\"undefined\":\"mce-enable\"}],\"num\":0}\";}i:3;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:3:\"cta\";s:4:\"size\";s:3:\"100\";s:5:\"title\";s:75:\"Like This Amazing Theme? Get ÜberShop and Start Selling Your Products Now!\";s:7:\"content\";s:158:\"{\"data\":[{\"bg_color\":\"#16c9c9\",\"cta_button_text\":\"Buy ÜberShop\",\"cta_button_link\":\"http://themeforest.net/user/pukkathemes\",\"text_color\":\"#ffffff\"}],\"num\":0}\";}i:4;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:4:\"size\";s:3:\"100\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"content\";s:120:\"{\"data\":[{\"bg_color\":\"\",\"text_content\":\"<p><a name=\\\"faq\\\"></a></p>\",\"text_color\":\"\",\"undefined\":\"mce-enable\"}],\"num\":0}\";}i:5;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";s:4:\"size\";s:3:\"100\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"content\";s:141:\"{\"data\":[{\"bg_color\":\"\",\"text_content\":\"<h1 style=\\\"text-align: center;\\\">&nbsp;FAQ</h1>\",\"text_color\":\"\",\"undefined\":\"mce-enable\"}],\"num\":0}\";}i:6;a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:9:\"accordion\";s:4:\"size\";s:3:\"100\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"content\";s:2175:\"{\"data\":[{\"text_title\":\"Lorem ipsum alpha acid abbey adjunct real ale reinheitsgebot autolysis \",\"text_content\":\"<p>&nbsp;lager ipa anaerobic dunkle caramel malt carboy crystal malt cold filter. alpha acid abbey adjunct real ale reinheitsgebot autolysis top-fermenting yeast pint glass sour/acidic enzymes length. sour/acidic rims pilsner bitter hydrometer heat exchanger. grainy balthazar abv wit scotch ale, trappist racking aroma hops mash tun real ale sparge crystal malt. tulip glass, barleywine aau, aroma hops pub lagering. degrees plato copper pitch sour/acidic chocolate malt: final gravity noble hops. aroma hops; gravity ibu balthazar noble hops lagering.</p>\",\"bg_color\":\"\",\"text_color\":\"\",\"undefined\":\"mce-enable\"},{\"text_title\":\"Lorem ipsum alpha acid abbey